WEBVTT

00:25.626 --> 00:27.728
'cause this is about
to be a good one.

00:27.861 --> 00:30.164
Down here in New Orleans,
you know we know how to party.

00:30.298 --> 00:31.699
And around here,
we like to say,

00:31.832 --> 00:33.567
"Laissez les
bons temps rouler."

00:35.803 --> 00:38.339
The wait is over.

00:38.472 --> 00:41.342
A sold-out Superdome
is the stage.

00:43.043 --> 00:46.380
After a year
of partially filled
or empty stadiums,

00:46.514 --> 00:49.016
this should be
absolutely electric.

00:49.150 --> 00:51.219
College football's Snickers
National Title game

00:51.352 --> 00:53.087
has finally arrived,

00:53.221 --> 00:55.256
and it is the matchup
of our dreams.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.091
We have the 13-1 Cougars

00:57.225 --> 00:59.460
going against
the undefeated Wolves,

00:59.593 --> 01:02.530
and this is where
legends are made.

01:02.663 --> 01:05.466
[Nick Wright] Wolves
quarterback, the Heisman
Trophy winner LeMarcus James.

01:05.599 --> 01:07.535
Possibly
the best quarterback

01:07.668 --> 01:10.238
to come into the NFL
since Patrick Mahomes.

01:10.371 --> 01:12.706
[reporter] And you know
who agrees with me
on that? Miami.

01:12.840 --> 01:15.243
'Cause they're poised to
take him number one overall,

01:15.376 --> 01:18.246
and I'm hearing for about
$35 million guaranteed.

01:18.379 --> 01:20.047
Meanwhile,
for the Cougars,

01:20.181 --> 01:21.815
you have running back
Cecil Burgess,

01:21.949 --> 01:23.717
AKA the Haitian Hammer.

01:23.851 --> 01:26.120
He's gonna run for,
eh, I don't know,

01:26.254 --> 01:28.822
200 to 400 yards
every game.

01:28.956 --> 01:30.458
That's how he set
the Big 12

01:30.591 --> 01:32.092
all-time single-season
rushing record.

01:32.226 --> 01:34.328
But the people
who really build

01:34.462 --> 01:36.764
the college football
dynasties are the coaches.

01:36.897 --> 01:40.468
We are not talking enough
about Wolves coach
James Lazor.

01:40.601 --> 01:44.104
Everybody knows the guy is
an elite program builder,

01:44.238 --> 01:46.940
one of the best coaches
we've seen,

01:47.074 --> 01:50.010
but he has never
won the big game.

01:50.144 --> 01:53.247
Monday night is about etching
his name in the history books.

01:55.149 --> 01:57.017
[Wright] You have
legacies on the line.

01:57.151 --> 01:59.119
You have controversies
surrounding the sport
as a whole.

01:59.253 --> 02:02.656
Monday cannot get here
soon enough

02:02.790 --> 02:05.793
for the college football
national title game.

02:14.034 --> 02:15.836
[person coughs]

02:15.969 --> 02:17.338
[tapping]

02:17.471 --> 02:18.606
[person sniffs]

02:21.709 --> 02:24.077
[tapping continues
intermittently]

02:31.652 --> 02:33.187
[exhales forcefully]

02:55.643 --> 02:57.378
[person] You hear that?

02:58.446 --> 03:00.281
The poppin'?
[bones popping]

03:03.817 --> 03:07.054
Was an elbow-to-helmet with
Michigan State's Will backer.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.357
I-right, simple, 68 blast.

03:09.490 --> 03:11.091
[football taps]
Wham.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.895
Darn thing
ain't been right since.

03:16.497 --> 03:17.865
[LeMarcus] Lead.

03:18.899 --> 03:19.967
Hmm?

03:20.668 --> 03:22.236
It was 1-41 lead.

03:24.104 --> 03:25.806
Hmm, pretty sure...

03:25.939 --> 03:29.310
If you were
on the second level,
then you were lead blocking.

03:29.443 --> 03:32.546
Michigan State ran
a Chicago 53
with a robber in the box.

03:34.014 --> 03:36.550
I mean, no way you got to
the Will back on the blast.

03:36.684 --> 03:38.185
Hmm?

03:38.319 --> 03:39.920
Could've been lead.

03:44.157 --> 03:45.859
[LeMarcus sighs]

03:52.533 --> 03:56.304
"The path
of the righteous man

03:57.938 --> 04:00.308
is beset on all sides

04:00.441 --> 04:02.310
by the inequities
of the selfish

04:03.477 --> 04:06.113
and the tyranny
of evil men."

04:08.882 --> 04:11.285
"Blessed is he who,
in the name of good will,

04:11.419 --> 04:13.421
shepherds the weak through
the valley of darkness."

04:13.554 --> 04:14.855
Hmm?

04:14.988 --> 04:16.624
"For he is
his brother's keeper

04:16.757 --> 04:18.459
and the finder
of lost children."

04:18.592 --> 04:22.796
"And I will strike them down
with vengeance
and furious anger

04:22.930 --> 04:26.266
those who attempt to poison
and destroy my brothers."

04:26.400 --> 04:29.670
[both] "And you will know
my name is the Lord,

04:29.803 --> 04:32.706
for I lay my finger
upon thee."

04:33.641 --> 04:35.909
[both imitate gunshots, grunt]

04:38.245 --> 04:40.314
[gasps dramatically]

04:40.448 --> 04:43.150
[both laughing]

04:46.219 --> 04:47.721
You stupid, man.

04:48.822 --> 04:51.058
That was an Oscar-winning
performance.

04:51.191 --> 04:52.593
Shit.

04:52.726 --> 04:55.128
Ah, shit, ol' Quentin
sure can write 'em.

04:55.262 --> 04:56.997
Yeah, he can. [chuckles]

04:58.466 --> 05:00.133
Damn.

05:00.267 --> 05:03.971
Hey, you turn
your location services off?

05:04.905 --> 05:08.041
Yeah. On the iPad too.

05:08.175 --> 05:11.111
We can still call
this whole thing off.

05:11.244 --> 05:13.447
Chalk it up
as a research project.

05:14.915 --> 05:17.017
Get some grad credits
out of it.

05:17.150 --> 05:19.286
Hell, I think we'd be
halfway to our master's.

05:19.420 --> 05:20.721
[scoffs]

05:28.028 --> 05:29.830
Bow your head, man.

05:33.934 --> 05:35.369
[grunts softly]

05:36.704 --> 05:38.839
[LeMarcus sighs]

05:38.972 --> 05:43.811
God, give us the wisdom
to see the path
we must take,

05:43.944 --> 05:45.979
and give us the courage
to brave it.

05:47.014 --> 05:48.782
Make of us a light.

05:50.884 --> 05:52.620
Amen.
Amen.

05:56.056 --> 05:57.891
You're getting better
with that.

06:03.497 --> 06:04.698
[sighs]

06:13.006 --> 06:14.074
[sighs]

06:15.543 --> 06:16.744
We're live.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.652
We'd best
get a move-on then.

06:24.785 --> 06:27.988
Coach's gonna become
a heat-seeking missile
looking for you.

06:28.856 --> 06:29.890
Yeah.

06:31.158 --> 06:33.594
I just hope he understands
this ain't about him.

06:36.497 --> 06:39.199
[commentator on TV]
Burgess, able to break away,

06:39.332 --> 06:41.101
into the secondary.

06:41.234 --> 06:43.336
Breaks another tackle...
Stop right there, Lukie.

06:43.471 --> 06:45.238
[keyboard clacks]
Right there.

06:45.372 --> 06:47.941
This is
what I'm talking about.
Simple stretch sweep to 34.

06:48.075 --> 06:49.943
Lukie, zoom on 34.

06:51.211 --> 06:54.548
There. Right ankle dominant cut
around the left corner.

06:54.682 --> 06:56.383
The best running back
in the country

06:56.517 --> 06:59.252
is turning the corner
on an inside ankle lead.

06:59.386 --> 07:01.989
Why? 34's left ankle
ain't right.

07:02.122 --> 07:03.891
It hasn't been
since week ten.

07:04.024 --> 07:06.860
Okay, real quick.
Cecil scores
on this play, right?

07:06.994 --> 07:09.563
Yeah. Eighty-yard sprint,
where he outruns a free safety.

07:09.697 --> 07:11.899
Yeah, against Vanderbilt,
I could outrun a free safety.

07:12.032 --> 07:15.202
So here's what we do.
If we move Cornelius
to the middle,

07:15.335 --> 07:16.637
we pinch in the OLBs,

07:16.770 --> 07:18.872
we got our safeties thinking
run support first.

07:19.006 --> 07:20.841
Cornelius will
eat his lunch,

07:20.974 --> 07:23.210
and we will shut 34 down
for the night.

07:23.343 --> 07:24.512
I got you.

07:24.645 --> 07:26.947
Boys. Booster club dinner.
Five minutes.

07:27.080 --> 07:29.449
Yeah, yeah, they can wait.
No, they cannot wait.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.384
They're the team owners.
You're the guest of honor.

07:31.519 --> 07:33.353
Luke can babysit the film,
right, baby?

07:33.487 --> 07:35.288
Tell you what. You can
come back here tonight.

07:35.422 --> 07:37.891
You guys can touch
and watch film
all night long. How's that?

07:38.025 --> 07:40.460
Seventy-two hours till
the national goddamn title game,

07:40.594 --> 07:43.063
and I got to parade around
in this dog-and-pony show.

07:43.196 --> 07:45.198
Heavy is the head that wears
the crown, my Lord.

07:45.332 --> 07:47.100
All right, look, I gotta
go get dressed, man,

07:47.234 --> 07:49.436
get ready for this
dog-and-pony show,
as you call it.

07:49.570 --> 07:51.639
Seriously, you're not going
to back me up here at all?

07:51.772 --> 07:53.607
No, I'm not.
I just do your defense.

07:53.741 --> 07:56.443
That's your own offense.
That's your life offense.

07:56.577 --> 07:58.478
[laughs]
Defense right here.

07:58.612 --> 08:00.280
I made these
short and sweet,
like you like it.

08:00.413 --> 08:02.149
I suggest you do the same
with your jokes.

08:02.282 --> 08:04.852
My jokes are hilarious,
and people love them.
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

08:07.287 --> 08:09.489
Stop.
Personal phone.

08:09.623 --> 08:12.192
Give me the personal phone.
Luke gets the business phone.

08:12.325 --> 08:14.027
Give him
the business phone.

08:14.161 --> 08:15.963
Anything comes in,
you know where to find me.

08:16.096 --> 08:18.365
You need to relax.
Let's enjoy the mountaintop.

08:18.498 --> 08:21.368
I'll enjoy the mountaintop
when we are at the mountaintop.
We're not there yet.

08:21.501 --> 08:23.403
Let's go. Can we go?

08:23.537 --> 08:24.872
Yes. Okay.

08:25.005 --> 08:26.640
Lukie, set all staff
for00 a.m.

08:26.774 --> 08:29.309
Bed check on time.
On time.

08:29.442 --> 08:30.711
Will do.

08:32.412 --> 08:34.247
[person]
Bed check. Let's go!

08:34.381 --> 08:36.249
[indistinct chattering]

08:40.453 --> 08:42.522
Hey, guys,
get in y'all room, man.
[knock on door]

08:43.791 --> 08:45.358
-What up, Scotty?
-Yo, what up, Orlando?

08:45.492 --> 08:47.394
Is Walton in there too?
Yeah, he in the bathroom.

08:47.527 --> 08:48.696
Let's get some rest.

08:48.829 --> 08:50.263
Talk to you later, man.
For sure.

08:50.397 --> 08:52.600
[laughing, chattering]
[bottles clink]

08:52.733 --> 08:55.468
Hey, Coach, check them
back there for me.
Sure.

08:56.937 --> 08:58.238
[knocks]

08:58.371 --> 09:00.874
Yo, LJ, Em.
It's Scotty. Open up.

09:03.010 --> 09:05.078
Come on, guys,
stop playing. Open up.

09:24.865 --> 09:26.767
[foil crinkling]

09:31.238 --> 09:33.240
[cell phone ringing]

09:33.373 --> 09:34.775
That's bed check.

09:37.678 --> 09:38.946
Yo, Scotty.

09:40.413 --> 09:41.949
I'm already asleep, man.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.017
Yeah. Sunday's snoring
like an ox.

09:44.151 --> 09:46.253
Can you hear him?
[imitates snoring]

09:47.587 --> 09:49.089
He broke his nose
so many times,

09:49.222 --> 09:51.058
once he gets
on his back,
I'm screwed.

09:51.191 --> 09:54.261
Yeah.00 a.m. sprints
in the bubble.

09:54.394 --> 09:55.629
Got it.

09:56.830 --> 09:58.265
He buy it?
Hell, yeah.

10:03.270 --> 10:06.573
Thank God Snickers sponsored
this game and not
some insurance company.

10:08.241 --> 10:09.242
You hungry?

10:09.376 --> 10:10.577
No.

10:12.713 --> 10:14.581
[sighs]

10:25.092 --> 10:26.927
[laughter]
[Coach Lazor]
I'm telling you,

10:27.060 --> 10:29.730
I know they don't have
boosters this good looking
in the Big 12.

10:29.863 --> 10:32.700
[all laughing]
I know the Cougars
don't look this good.

10:34.267 --> 10:36.336
We have built this program
into a juggernaut.

10:36.469 --> 10:39.206
Two consecutive
conference championships,

10:39.339 --> 10:41.174
two consecutive
play-off berths,

10:41.308 --> 10:43.010
and now...
[audience applauding]

10:43.143 --> 10:45.412
...for the first time
in program history,

10:46.847 --> 10:50.117
we are headed to our first
national title game.

10:50.250 --> 10:52.085
[cheering]

10:54.988 --> 10:56.790
All of you in this room,

10:56.924 --> 10:59.760
you have supported,
pushed and prodded,

10:59.893 --> 11:02.362
and sometimes much,
much worse.

11:02.495 --> 11:04.798
[laughing]
But I appreciate it.

11:04.932 --> 11:07.034
That's how you grow.

11:07.167 --> 11:10.570
And I appreciate the opportunity
to have presided over this,

11:10.704 --> 11:14.507
to help young men
become champions

11:14.641 --> 11:16.777
on and off
the football field.

11:16.910 --> 11:18.245
Go, Pack!

11:18.378 --> 11:20.380
[cheering]

11:22.182 --> 11:24.484
[music playing on speakers]
[indistinct chattering]

11:30.490 --> 11:32.893
You're seriously pressing
your bet again?

11:33.026 --> 11:35.162
Half a million dollars?

11:35.295 --> 11:37.564
Come on, Roger, you know me.
It's for the title.

11:37.697 --> 11:40.167
Go big or go home,
and I ain't fucking leaving.

11:40.300 --> 11:43.370
Well, the apple sure
didn't fall far
from the tree with you.

11:43.503 --> 11:45.538
God bless
your daddy's soul.

11:45.672 --> 11:49.009
Old Fred used to like to
bet the house in Vegas.
[chuckles]

11:49.142 --> 11:51.178
He just liked
the free drinks.
Well, hear, hear.

11:51.311 --> 11:53.580
Question is,
how in the glorious hell

11:53.713 --> 11:55.348
are we gonna stop
Cecil Burgess?

11:55.482 --> 11:57.184
Fastest I seen
since Herschel.

11:57.317 --> 11:58.618
It's me,

11:58.752 --> 12:00.420
I'm flooding the gaps,

12:00.553 --> 12:02.489
bringing Mack
from the strong side

12:02.622 --> 12:05.058
and feeding Cornelius
raw meat till kickoff.

12:05.192 --> 12:07.427
Or we break in his room
and Tonya Harding
that son of a bitch.

12:07.560 --> 12:09.930
Now, aren't you sweet?
[chuckles]

12:10.063 --> 12:11.932
Well, as long as we got
LeMarcus back there

12:12.065 --> 12:14.234
firing bullets,
we'll be fine--
better than fine.

12:14.367 --> 12:16.870
Coach, we was just talking
about LeMarcus.

12:17.004 --> 12:18.171
LeMarcus who?

12:18.305 --> 12:19.706
[laughter]
But I'll tell you what,

12:19.840 --> 12:22.075
he was pretty raw
when we found him,

12:22.209 --> 12:26.179
and obviously, he's
developed into something
really, really special.

12:26.313 --> 12:29.616
You think you can convince him
he ain't ready to jump
for another year?

12:29.749 --> 12:31.952
I'm just gonna support
whatever is best for LeMarcus.

12:32.085 --> 12:33.854
[Rodger] Amen.
[Taylor] Coach,
I got a kid in Little Rock.

12:33.987 --> 12:35.923
Hell of an arm. Got to show
you some videos of him.

12:36.056 --> 12:38.725
[Coach Lazor] Love to see it.
You remember
the bad old days

12:38.859 --> 12:40.794
when we were scraping
the bottom of the barrel,

12:40.928 --> 12:44.431
begging JUCO transfers
with cases of Budweiser

12:44.564 --> 12:46.066
and jobs
with the dealership?

12:46.199 --> 12:48.101
[Coach Lazor]
Yeah, all too well.

12:48.235 --> 12:50.303
[Taylor] And all that changed
once you got LeMarcus.
[Rodger] Bullshit.

12:50.437 --> 12:52.339
All that changed
when we got Coach here.

12:52.472 --> 12:54.274
Hey, Coach.
Kevin McDonald.
Hi, Kevin.

12:54.407 --> 12:55.809
Director of Communication
for the CFP.

12:55.943 --> 12:57.544
Good to meet you,
and thanks for everything.

12:57.677 --> 13:01.014
Sure. Uh, we may have
a situation.

13:01.148 --> 13:04.317
LeMarcus just tweeted this
earlier tonight.

13:05.718 --> 13:08.421
It says he's boycotting
the game.

13:08.555 --> 13:11.091
Reporters are
already swarming.

13:11.224 --> 13:13.793
We're trying to keep them
off the players' floor.

13:13.927 --> 13:16.596
Can probably do that
till morning,

13:16.729 --> 13:18.665
but this can get
out of hand fast.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.433
It won't.
Give me 20 minutes.

13:27.240 --> 13:29.476
Guys, I'll see you right back.
[chuckles]

13:40.753 --> 13:41.889
Hey.

13:43.290 --> 13:44.657
Hi.

13:46.026 --> 13:48.395
A poet at a football game.

13:49.662 --> 13:51.865
Philosopher
at a football game.

13:51.999 --> 13:54.134
[both chuckle]
Anyway...

13:57.204 --> 13:58.939
You look fantastic.

14:00.440 --> 14:02.709
[chuckles]

14:02.842 --> 14:05.812
Scotty, we sure
this is the room?
Yeah, Coach.

14:05.946 --> 14:08.181
Okay, and they were here
at bed check?

14:08.315 --> 14:10.683
Yeah, they're marked off.
What the fuck does that mean,
"They're marked off"?

14:10.817 --> 14:13.220
Did somebody see 'em?
No. But I spoke to LJ
on the phone.

14:13.353 --> 14:15.288
What the fuck?
You ain't seen nobody...

14:15.422 --> 14:17.357
You don't do bed check
on the goddamn telephone.

14:17.490 --> 14:19.426
You check the goddamn bed.
For Christ's sake.

14:19.559 --> 14:22.229
Goddamn it!
Bailey's got my phone.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.497
Your work one.
Yes. Thank you.

14:24.631 --> 14:26.599
Jesus Christ, man.
We're in New Orleans.

14:26.733 --> 14:29.469
Walking distance
to the Quarter
with LeMarcus James.

14:29.602 --> 14:33.273
You might want to actually check
that he's in bed at bed check.

14:33.406 --> 14:35.542
When's the last time
did y'all see him?
Come on, now.

14:35.675 --> 14:37.710
Huh?
When he got off the bus.

14:37.844 --> 14:40.513
Hey, LeMarcus, it's Coach.
Just hit me back here
on the work cell, okay?

14:40.647 --> 14:42.349
If you're out and about,
no problem.

14:42.482 --> 14:44.384
Just, uh, checking in, okay?

14:44.517 --> 14:46.253
We'll see you
for a.m. sprints, man.

14:46.386 --> 14:48.421
Goddamn it.
There's the guy
with the key, Coach.

14:48.555 --> 14:49.957
I'm sorry.

14:50.090 --> 14:51.424
All right.

14:52.659 --> 14:53.826
[sighs]

14:53.961 --> 14:55.495
LeMarcus. Emmett.

14:57.597 --> 14:59.566
Goddamn it.

14:59.699 --> 15:01.601
What the...

15:01.734 --> 15:05.438
Well, I guess we just knock
on every goddamn door
at the hotel.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.674
We got to find him.
Let's go. Go, go, go.

15:07.807 --> 15:09.576
Wake everybody up
if you have to.

15:09.709 --> 15:11.011
Shit.

15:11.144 --> 15:13.813
[indistinct conversations]

15:21.921 --> 15:25.358
[Coach Dunn]
Come on, Cornelius,
open up the door. Hey.

15:25.492 --> 15:27.927
Fuck. Hold on.
[bottle clinks]

15:29.196 --> 15:30.763
What do you want, Coach?

15:32.432 --> 15:34.434
What the fuck
is that smell?

15:34.567 --> 15:36.769
That's Payton's ass
after Popeyes.

15:38.071 --> 15:41.141
There something you need?
Look, have you
seen LeMarcus?

15:41.274 --> 15:43.143
Why the fuck
would I know where he's at?

15:43.276 --> 15:45.412
What's going on?
It's nothing for you
to worry about.

15:45.545 --> 15:47.414
Just be ready for sprints
in the morning.

15:47.547 --> 15:49.482
Nasty-ass kids.

16:06.966 --> 16:08.368
[LeMarcus] Yo, Orlando.

16:11.404 --> 16:12.972
How drunk are you, man?

16:13.973 --> 16:15.942
I haven't drank
in four months.

16:16.076 --> 16:17.177
Where's your phone?

16:17.310 --> 16:19.912
In the room, like you asked.

16:20.047 --> 16:22.015
But what the fuck
is this, LJ?

16:22.849 --> 16:24.817
It's exactly what I said.

16:24.951 --> 16:26.753
I ain't playing
until they pay us.

16:26.886 --> 16:28.488
What? You broke again?

16:28.621 --> 16:31.058
You hurt?
I'm done.

16:31.191 --> 16:34.161
They're here making billions
while the rest of us
make scraps.

16:34.294 --> 16:38.131
Me and you, we could sell
our names. What about
everybody else, huh?

