43:54.800 --> 43:56.601
And helped refinance
your mother's mortgage

43:56.735 --> 43:58.970
when she fell behind,
and also with your brother.

43:59.104 --> 44:02.741
-Should we talk
about the message--
-Don't... say another word.

44:05.243 --> 44:06.812
And don't do this.

44:06.945 --> 44:08.814
You don't give a shit
about us.

44:08.947 --> 44:12.317
-All you give a shit about
is your damn game.
-Now, now, now, Taylor.

44:14.786 --> 44:17.322
LeMarcus, what--
what's going on here?

44:17.455 --> 44:19.190
Me and you are buddies.

44:19.324 --> 44:21.192
You love playing football.

44:21.326 --> 44:23.361
Hell, I love watching you
play football.

44:23.494 --> 44:26.664
An entire college campus,
40,000 kids,

44:26.798 --> 44:28.934
thinks that you're
Jesus Christ incarnate.

44:29.067 --> 44:32.170
What's going on?
You need money?

44:33.171 --> 44:35.206
Just tell me
where to send the check.

44:36.742 --> 44:38.509
What the fuck
don't you get?

44:42.447 --> 44:43.882
You ever read The Jungle?

44:44.015 --> 44:46.084
What has that got to do
with anything, LeMarcus?

44:46.217 --> 44:47.819
The American Dream.

44:49.387 --> 44:51.723
This guy Jurgis
from Lithuania,

44:51.857 --> 44:54.092
he worked
at the meat-packing plant
in Chicago.

44:54.225 --> 44:56.127
Now, Jurgis was young,

44:56.261 --> 44:58.163
he was bigger, stronger
than the rest of 'em.

44:58.296 --> 45:00.198
So they put him
to work in the kill beds.

45:00.331 --> 45:02.834
He worked so hard,
he couldn't bend
his fingers.

45:02.968 --> 45:06.071
He couldn't flex his knees,
broke his ankle.

45:06.204 --> 45:08.673
After all those years,
he just kept on working,

45:08.807 --> 45:11.009
and he loved it.

45:11.142 --> 45:14.880
See, that didn't mean shit
to the guys who owned
the plant though, did it?

45:15.013 --> 45:18.483
'Cause they weren't
about to take care
of no broke immigrant.

45:19.550 --> 45:23.054
LeMarcus... [sighs]
You ain't that guy.

45:23.188 --> 45:25.924
You're about to be
the number one pick

45:26.057 --> 45:28.259
in the first round
of the NFL draft,

45:28.393 --> 45:31.830
-and Miami is gonna
pay you $35 million...
-Yeah, I know.

45:31.963 --> 45:33.698
That's a whole lot of meat.

45:33.832 --> 45:36.868
What about the guys
who ain't going
into the League?

45:37.002 --> 45:39.737
The guys who busted
their head in the dirt
for the last four years,

45:39.871 --> 45:42.273
only to wind up
mangled and broke?
What about them, huh?

45:42.407 --> 45:45.610
-So this whole thing's
about you?
-It's about everyone, man.

45:45.743 --> 45:47.946
What the fuck do you think
you're gonna do?

45:48.079 --> 45:50.548
You can't square off
with the entire system.

45:50.681 --> 45:53.418
You two cannot
unionize college sports,
and that's a fact.

45:54.853 --> 45:56.788
-It ain't two.
-What?

45:56.922 --> 45:59.224
It ain't just two of us
no more,

45:59.357 --> 46:00.758
and that's a fact.

46:04.195 --> 46:05.563
[sighs]

46:11.236 --> 46:13.571
[person] We have to
dismantle the structure

46:13.704 --> 46:15.273
and do something
that's more equitable,

46:15.406 --> 46:16.975
that's fairer
for these athletes.

46:17.108 --> 46:18.810
I've got teammates
that I played

46:18.944 --> 46:20.912
collegiate ball with
at Ohio State

46:21.046 --> 46:22.747
that suffered some
career-ending injuries,

46:22.881 --> 46:24.983
some life-altering
injuries,

46:25.116 --> 46:27.318
that struggle
and still struggle today

46:27.452 --> 46:30.088
without any support
from the university.

46:30.221 --> 46:31.789
It's very frustrating.

46:31.923 --> 46:33.658
So I'm proud
to stand behind

46:33.791 --> 46:35.793
LeMarcus James
and what he's doing.

46:35.927 --> 46:38.563
