Orlando Bishop
just tweeted this.

1:08:19.329 --> 1:08:20.797
He's out.
[Everly] That's cute.

1:08:20.930 --> 1:08:22.899
We got four players
threatening to walk now too.

1:08:23.032 --> 1:08:24.434
How are these two
even doing this?

1:08:24.568 --> 1:08:26.069
I still think
Coach Lazor's the one

1:08:26.203 --> 1:08:27.804
to talk LeMarcus
off this ledge.

1:08:27.937 --> 1:08:29.973
He walks him back,
they'll all follow.

1:08:30.106 --> 1:08:31.875
Where's your coach now?

1:08:32.008 --> 1:08:34.344
He's, uh,
taking a minute.

1:08:34.478 --> 1:08:35.812
[Katherine]
He's tanking.

1:08:35.945 --> 1:08:37.747
He's fine.
[Mike] What does he need?

1:08:37.881 --> 1:08:39.749
A divorce lawyer.
[Everly chuckles]

1:08:39.883 --> 1:08:42.252
[Everly] He's fine, I said.
Lazor or no Lazor,

1:08:42.386 --> 1:08:43.920
we're putting two teams
on the field tomorrow,

1:08:44.053 --> 1:08:46.022
even if we gotta dress
the damn cheerleaders.

1:08:46.156 --> 1:08:48.292
Who's second in line
if Lazor can't go?

1:08:48.425 --> 1:08:52.362
I guess, uh, Ronnie Dunn,
defensive coordinator.

1:08:52.496 --> 1:08:54.431
You trust him?
Yeah. Company man.

1:08:54.564 --> 1:08:56.433
Been at the university
since a player himself,

1:08:56.566 --> 1:08:58.335
so, yeah, he'll take
marching orders.

1:08:58.468 --> 1:09:00.770
-You sure?
-This a fucking inquisition?

1:09:00.904 --> 1:09:04.374
I don't trust anyone
with a vested pension
and Medicare.

1:09:05.575 --> 1:09:07.277
Oh, God. You know what?

1:09:07.411 --> 1:09:09.479
Fuck you very much.

1:09:09.613 --> 1:09:12.916
All right? I need this shit
like I need a third tit.

1:09:13.049 --> 1:09:15.352
I will march
my entire conference

1:09:15.485 --> 1:09:16.986
right out that door,

1:09:17.120 --> 1:09:21.525
put together
my own play-offs
without any of you.

1:09:21.658 --> 1:09:23.126
How do you like me?

1:09:23.260 --> 1:09:25.329
You'd be in breach
of 16 different contracts,

1:09:25.462 --> 1:09:29.132
squander a $100-million payday
for tomorrow alone.

1:09:29.266 --> 1:09:32.502
Not to mention what I imagine
would be a full audit

1:09:32.636 --> 1:09:35.772
of SEC expenses
under your tenure.

1:09:35.905 --> 1:09:38.808
You know, to make sure
that those band fields,
softball stadiums

1:09:38.942 --> 1:09:42.679
and turquoise-green
Bermuda sod
weren't really just

1:09:42.812 --> 1:09:46.182
high-paid escorts
in New York City

1:09:46.316 --> 1:09:49.419
at the Bemelman Bar
of the Carlyle.

1:09:53.557 --> 1:09:56.493
Bouncing 'em
out of your apartment
three at a time, right?

1:10:04.634 --> 1:10:06.202
Fuck you.

1:10:06.803 --> 1:10:07.871
[scoffs]

1:10:09.273 --> 1:10:10.507
Hoo!

1:10:15.645 --> 1:10:17.847
[person] We're still
24 hours away

1:10:17.981 --> 1:10:20.183
from the Snickers
National Title game.

1:10:20.317 --> 1:10:22.252
-Only the biggest game...
-[person 2] Man, these guys

1:10:22.386 --> 1:10:23.920
are already getting
free education.

1:10:24.053 --> 1:10:26.222
Money is just
gonna ruin it.

1:10:26.356 --> 1:10:28.157
They aren't ready
for all that money.
I wasn't when I was 18.

1:10:28.292 --> 1:10:30.494
[person 3] I don't know
if this man is a racist,

1:10:30.627 --> 1:10:32.762
but what I do know
is that he made a fortune

1:10:32.896 --> 1:10:36.165
mostly off the backs
of young Black men.

1:10:37.301 --> 1:10:38.902
[Bailey] Question.

1:10:39.035 --> 1:10:41.405
If I hadn't stayed here
to explain to you

1:10:41.538 --> 1:10:44.974
that I was leaving,
would you have noticed
I'd gone?

1:10:46.776 --> 1:10:48.945
[panting]

1:11:07.130 --> 1:11:08.565
[indistinct chattering]

1:11:08.698 --> 1:11:10.634
[person]
Coach! Coach Lazor!

1:11:10.767 --> 1:11:13.303
-[person 2] Oh, my God.
Look, it's Coach Lazor.
-[people clamoring]

1:11:13.437 --> 1:11:15.305
[person 3] Hey, Coach,
can we get a picture?
Sorry, buddy.

1:11:15.439 --> 1:11:18.241
It's just really
not a good time, okay?
Sorry, sorry...

1:11:18.375 --> 1:11:21.077
-[clamoring continues]
-Okay, not now!

1:11:21.210 --> 1:11:24.481
Hey, give him some space.
Give him some space.

1:11:24.614 --> 1:11:26.082
No pictures! No pictures!

1:11:26.215 --> 1:11:27.551
Have a good game, Coach!

1:11:44.968 --> 1:11:47.537
[Everly] Now, I know for a fact
that LeMarcus and the guys,

1:11:47.671 --> 1:11:49.339
they respect
the hell out of you,

1:11:49.473 --> 1:11:54.778
and you would be the first
African-American head coach

1:11:54.911 --> 1:11:59.683
to lead a team onto the field
for a national title game.

1:12:00.517 --> 1:12:02.118
Hell,

1:12:02.251 --> 1:12:04.488
hopefully win the thing, huh?

1:12:04.621 --> 1:12:06.856
Let's make history together.

1:12:24.107 --> 1:12:26.476
The NCAA may have started
with this...

1:12:26.610 --> 1:12:28.712
[Emmett groans]
...imaginary
pie-in-the-sky idea

1:12:28.845 --> 1:12:31.280
that it was about amateurism,
and at one point it was.

1:12:31.415 --> 1:12:34.818
But then there was a turn,
and it became about money.

1:12:34.951 --> 1:12:37.787
[knocking]
Plain and simple.
I thought this was America.

1:12:37.921 --> 1:12:39.656
[coughing]
Yeah?

1:12:39.789 --> 1:12:41.558
It's Coach Dunn.

1:12:43.259 --> 1:12:45.061
[Emmett] You all
by your lonesome?

1:12:45.194 --> 1:12:47.664
[groans]
[Coach Dunn]
It's just me.

1:12:47.797 --> 1:12:49.533
[door unlocks]

1:12:50.534 --> 1:12:51.568
Coach?

1:12:51.701 --> 1:12:54.370
You two are really hard
to find.

1:12:54.504 --> 1:12:57.340
It's easier to find Bigfoot
than to find you two.

1:12:58.341 --> 1:13:00.043
Look, relax.
I won't tell Lazor.

1:13:01.010 --> 1:13:02.846
[chuckles softly]
You know something?

1:13:02.979 --> 1:13:05.381
I gotta give credit
to you two, actually.

1:13:05.515 --> 1:13:08.051
I'm really surprised
you was able to pull this off.

1:13:10.086 --> 1:13:11.788
But you got trouble.

1:13:12.989 --> 1:13:15.091
Yep, they still gonna
play the game.

1:13:17.561 --> 1:13:19.095
With 19 freshmen?

1:13:19.996 --> 1:13:21.531
Cornelius?

1:13:21.665 --> 1:13:23.366
They don't care who plays
as long as it's on TV.

1:13:23.500 --> 1:13:25.569
[Emmett scoffs]

1:13:25.702 --> 1:13:27.571
The shit bowl.

1:13:27.704 --> 1:13:29.706
[Coach Dunn] They shitting
their pants right now.

1:13:29.839 --> 1:13:31.875
They got so desperate,
they approached me

1:13:32.008 --> 1:13:33.943
and said
If Lazor doesn't show up,

1:13:34.077 --> 1:13:36.012
I can bring the team
out to the field.

1:13:37.180 --> 1:13:39.082
So, Coach is sitting?

1:13:39.215 --> 1:13:41.084
[sighs] I don't know, man.
It's really hard
to tell right now,

1:13:41.217 --> 1:13:42.919
but it looks like it.

1:13:43.052 --> 1:13:44.020
Damn.

1:13:44.153 --> 1:13:46.322
So, what you gonna do?

1:13:46.456 --> 1:13:48.992
The first Black head coach
in a national title game?

1:13:49.125 --> 1:13:50.827
It's a big deal.

1:13:52.095 --> 1:13:55.331
I ain't no fucking pawn.
Hell, no, I'm not doing it.

1:13:55.465 --> 1:13:57.433
I'm one of best defensive
coaches in this country.

1:13:57.567 --> 1:13:58.935
I don't need
no fucking handouts.

1:13:59.068 --> 1:14:00.470
Amen, Coach.

1:14:00.604 --> 1:14:02.071
We feel the same way.

1:14:02.205 --> 1:14:04.340
Even if this whole thing
goes up in a ball of flames,

1:14:04.474 --> 1:14:06.242
we're not stepping
on that field.

1:14:08.745 --> 1:14:11.581
Look, y'all.
Have I ever told you
the Hannibal Lawson story?

1:14:11.715 --> 1:14:13.850
Who?
Hannibal Lawson.

1:14:13.983 --> 1:14:17.053
So, Han Lawson, to me, was one
of the best defensive tackles

1:14:17.186 --> 1:14:18.922
in Louisiana
high school history.

1:14:19.055 --> 1:14:20.824
He went on to LSU.

1:14:20.957 --> 1:14:22.926
You know, a bright future.

1:14:24.027 --> 1:14:25.762
He got his knee shredded
in practice.

1:14:25.895 --> 1:14:28.598
And the result of that,
they took his scholarship away.

1:14:30.900 --> 1:14:32.769
But Hannibal did
something interesting.

1:14:32.902 --> 1:14:35.805
He hired
a lawyer in a cheap suit
with some night-school degree,

1:14:35.939 --> 1:14:38.675
and he sued the NCAA
for workmen's comp.

1:14:38.808 --> 1:14:40.677
-Smart, right?
-Yeah.

1:14:40.810 --> 1:14:43.112
Went all the way to
the Louisiana Supreme Court.

1:14:43.246 --> 1:14:44.914
[Emmett] What happened?

1:14:45.048 --> 1:14:46.816
Student-athlete.

1:14:46.950 --> 1:14:49.285
[Coach Dunn]
Yeah, they said he was nothing
but a student-athlete.

1:14:49.418 --> 1:14:51.454
They didn't consider him
an employee, even though
they were selling

1:14:51.588 --> 1:14:53.222
hundreds and thousands
of tickets

1:14:53.356 --> 1:14:55.892
every fucking Saturday,
making millions of dollars!

1:14:56.025 --> 1:14:59.529
You're breaking your body
every fucking practice
and every game.

1:14:59.663 --> 1:15:02.298
And whenever they decide
to take the scholarship
away from you, they can,

1:15:02.431 --> 1:15:03.967
whenever the fuck
they feel like it.

1:15:04.100 --> 1:15:06.903
That's a crazy,
sick system.

1:15:07.036 --> 1:15:10.206
And maybe you two
will change it.
I don't know.

1:15:10.339 --> 1:15:13.977
But I want y'all to understand
something. There's a lot
of Han Lawsons out here.

1:15:15.211 --> 1:15:16.646
Survival of the fittest.

1:15:18.347 --> 1:15:20.116
America.

1:15:21.585 --> 1:15:23.553
This little pigskin football
right here

1:15:23.687 --> 1:15:25.054
holds a lot of weight to it.

1:15:25.188 --> 1:15:26.956
It's more than a game.

1:15:27.090 --> 1:15:28.892
It's a fucking business.

1:15:33.429 --> 1:15:34.798
Hey, Coach.

1:15:35.832 --> 1:15:37.567
Thank you.

1:15:38.534 --> 1:15:40.003
Good luck, fellas.

1:15:41.304 --> 1:15:43.206
[coughs]

1:15:46.342 --> 1:15:48.544
[sighs]
[door closes]

1:15:48.678 --> 1:15:50.513
We're gonna need Cecil
on board.

1:15:50.647 --> 1:15:54.183
We both don't play,
the advertisers
will start pulling out.

1:15:55.518 --> 1:15:56.920
It's the only way.

1:15:57.921 --> 1:16:00.023
[blues rock music playing]

1:16:00.156 --> 1:16:02.358
[Rodgers] Take a little more
of the edge off.

1:16:04.260 --> 1:16:06.395
Gotta let it out.

1:16:06.529 --> 1:16:09.398
If you don't,
it just stays inside you,
it becomes poison.

1:16:09.532 --> 1:16:11.234
[Taylor sighs]

1:16:11.367 --> 1:16:14.070
Okay, what's the plan?
Damn it.

1:16:14.203 --> 1:16:16.139
I can't even focus
on that right now.

1:16:16.272 --> 1:16:19.575
Well, you... you got to.
You gotta bifurcate.

1:16:19.709 --> 1:16:23.947
Uh, I don't know what
that means, but I think
I get the gist of it.

1:16:24.080 --> 1:16:25.915
About to lose 500,000
'cause of LeMarcus.

1:16:26.049 --> 1:16:27.116
[Rodgers] Taylor.
He fucked us.

1:16:27.250 --> 1:16:28.551
-Put the phone down.
-He fucked us.

1:16:28.685 --> 1:16:30.353
-Put the phone down.
-All right.

1:16:30.486 --> 1:16:33.022
Coach, I know you don't want
to hear this right now.

1:16:33.156 --> 1:16:36.092
I've been married
three times myself.

1:16:36.225 --> 1:16:38.394
But the hurt goes away.

1:16:38.527 --> 1:16:39.796
Poof.

1:16:39.929 --> 1:16:41.965
One day, just like that.
Gone.

1:16:42.098 --> 1:16:44.801
I'm telling you,
Bailey's my one and only.

1:16:44.934 --> 1:16:47.937
And she's gone.
And it's my own goddamn fault.

1:16:48.071 --> 1:16:49.639
[Taylor] Coach,
no offense at all.

1:16:49.773 --> 1:16:51.708
Your love life,
that's your thing.

1:16:51.841 --> 1:16:53.309
Your racial views,
that's your thing.

1:16:53.442 --> 1:16:55.845
But we have
a national title
in less than 24 hours.

1:16:55.979 --> 1:16:58.281
Can you please
just focus on that?
Fucking racial views?

1:16:58.414 --> 1:16:59.916
First of all,
one goddamn reporter

1:17:00.049 --> 1:17:01.484
baits me into saying
something stupid.

1:17:01.617 --> 1:17:03.119
I know
you're not racist.

1:17:03.252 --> 1:17:04.854
I'm just saying we got
the game to focus on, okay?

1:17:04.988 --> 1:17:06.690
That's all I'm saying.
What fucking game?

1:17:06.823 --> 1:17:08.792
I don't have
a goddamn team.
Less than 24 hours.

1:17:08.925 --> 1:17:12.128
I'm supposed
to walk out of that tunnel
with-- with freshmen.

1:17:12.261 --> 1:17:14.698
Nobody's askin' you...
and go in there and get
our ass kicked?

1:17:14.831 --> 1:17:17.533
You gotta figure it out.
That's not competition.
That's a fucking slaughter.

1:17:17.667 --> 1:17:19.168
I'm doing what I can.

1:17:19.302 --> 1:17:21.270
You gotta do better, Coach.
You're under contract.

1:17:21.404 --> 1:17:23.106
Con...
Fuck that contract.

1:17:23.239 --> 1:17:25.675
Are you talking to me
about the fucking contract
right now?

1:17:25.809 --> 1:17:27.310
I could walk
across the street tomorrow

1:17:27.443 --> 1:17:29.312
and get another contract
if they find me in breach.

1:17:29.445 --> 1:17:31.681
I don't give a shit.
I don't need
the goddamn money anyway.

1:17:31.815 --> 1:17:33.182
Coach,
you're hurtin' right now.

1:17:33.316 --> 1:17:36.519
Let's just give it
an hour or two.

1:17:36.652 --> 1:17:38.321
See the state of play.

1:17:38.454 --> 1:17:41.624
It's best not to make
any decisions feeling this way.

1:17:43.159 --> 1:17:44.694
Tell you what.
It's the ones

1:17:44.828 --> 1:17:47.630
that are closest to us
that hurt us the most.

1:18:06.449 --> 1:18:08.852
You as good
as they say you are?

1:18:08.985 --> 1:18:11.687
To which of my many talents
are you referring?

1:18:12.989 --> 1:18:15.391
There was a fight
that no one knows about.

1:18:15.524 --> 1:18:17.861
A real brawl.
A kid got hurt bad.

1:18:17.994 --> 1:18:21.197
I'll alert the authorities.
Oh, they know.

1:18:21.330 --> 1:18:24.734
He's blind in one eye now
and got a hole in his skull.

1:18:26.402 --> 1:18:29.405
But money talks,
and NDAs don't.

1:18:34.610 --> 1:18:36.045
I'm listening.

1:18:38.815 --> 1:18:40.183
LeMarcus.

1:18:42.285 --> 1:18:43.519
[shower running]

1:18:43.652 --> 1:18:46.422
[practicing Italian]

1:18:46.555 --> 1:18:49.325
Oh, crap,
I think I just called you
my pistachio. [laughs]

1:18:49.458 --> 1:18:52.929
Your phone sucks.
Is mine in there?

1:18:53.062 --> 1:18:54.663
It is here.

1:18:54.798 --> 1:18:56.532
[Bailey] Ah.

1:18:56.665 --> 1:18:59.803
You just got a text
from a guy
named Mike Titus.

1:18:59.936 --> 1:19:01.771
What? Crap.

1:19:01.905 --> 1:19:05.374
I just must have grabbed
James' personal one again
by accident.

1:19:05.508 --> 1:19:09.312
[Italian accent]
Can you bring it to me,
mi pistachio?

1:19:10.746 --> 1:19:12.782
It's probably goin' ape-shit
right now.

1:19:12.916 --> 1:19:14.918
After everything we've done
for LeMarcus.

1:19:15.051 --> 1:19:18.387
Every single one of those kids
are spoiled brats.

1:19:18.521 --> 1:19:20.423
Spoiled freaking brats.

1:19:20.556 --> 1:19:22.959
Geez. [chuckles]

1:19:23.092 --> 1:19:27.130
Oh, I cannot wait
to go to Rome.

1:19:27.263 --> 1:19:30.099
There's this one place
that I want to eat at,

1:19:30.233 --> 1:19:33.402
and they still have
the bullet holes
in the walls from the war.

1:19:33.536 --> 1:19:37.073
Do you see this?
Probably not,
'cause your phone stinks.

1:19:40.844 --> 1:19:41.945
What?

1:19:44.848 --> 1:19:46.782
I've been helping LeMarcus.

1:19:49.518 --> 1:19:51.254
What?

1:19:51.387 --> 1:19:53.156
You know, with his boycott.

1:19:53.289 --> 1:19:54.891
That's why I'm here.

1:19:56.525 --> 1:19:58.327
I don't get it.

1:20:00.329 --> 1:20:02.665
He came to me after class.

1:20:03.666 --> 1:20:05.134
And... [sighs]

1:20:06.235 --> 1:20:07.770
...what was I gonna do?

1:20:08.737 --> 1:20:10.706
Be another
tenured paper tiger?

1:20:12.275 --> 1:20:14.377
Teaching organized labor
five days a week,

1:20:14.510 --> 1:20:16.880
then hide behind my desk
when one of my own students

1:20:17.013 --> 1:20:19.182
actually wants
to do something about it?

1:20:21.084 --> 1:20:22.852
So...

1:20:22.986 --> 1:20:24.353
I helped him

1:20:25.488 --> 1:20:27.456
with his strategy

1:20:28.257 --> 1:20:29.893
any way I could.

1:20:31.961 --> 1:20:33.096
It's funny.

1:20:33.229 --> 1:20:35.331
LeMarcus knew
the rumors about us,

1:20:35.464 --> 1:20:37.200
like everybody else.

1:20:37.333 --> 1:20:39.135
Except your husband,
of course.

1:20:40.436 --> 1:20:43.672
And you, calling LeMarcus
a spoiled brat,

1:20:44.640 --> 1:20:48.211
especially when he has
so much to lose.

1:20:50.146 --> 1:20:53.682
Maybe you're more part
of the system than you think.
Get out.

1:20:55.818 --> 1:20:57.987
[voice breaking]
Get the fuck out of here.

1:21:02.658 --> 1:21:03.927
Leave!

1:21:14.670 --> 1:21:16.039
[door closes]

1:21:19.008 --> 1:21:20.076
[sobs]

1:21:27.016 --> 1:21:28.717
[whispers] Fuck me.

1:21:28.851 --> 1:21:30.019
[sobs]

1:21:47.971 --> 1:21:49.538
[knocking]

1:21:54.010 --> 1:21:55.678
[sighs]

1:22:05.588 --> 1:22:07.790
Oh, sorry. I think
we got the wrong room.

1:22:07.923 --> 1:22:09.792
No.
This room is Cecil's.

1:22:09.925 --> 1:22:12.261
Come in.
We don't have a lot of time.

1:22:20.569 --> 1:22:23.139
My name's Katherine Poe.
I come bearing gifts.

1:22:23.272 --> 1:22:25.241
You need my phone?

1:22:28.711 --> 1:22:30.013
You look rough.

1:22:30.146 --> 1:22:32.281
Just a cold.

1:22:32.415 --> 1:22:33.916
Where's Cecil?

1:22:34.050 --> 1:22:36.652
They're in a suite
ten floors up, playing 2K.

1:22:38.121 --> 1:22:39.588
No, wait.

1:22:39.722 --> 1:22:42.058
[chuckles] You haven't
even heard my offer yet.

1:22:42.191 --> 1:22:44.793
It's a pretty good offer.
A lot of wonderful things.

1:22:44.927 --> 1:22:46.662
A lot of meat
on the bone.

1:22:51.867 --> 1:22:53.436
Okay.

1:22:53.569 --> 1:22:55.404
What you got?

1:22:55.538 --> 1:22:57.840
I send the best concierge
doctor in New Orleans,

1:22:57.973 --> 1:22:59.608
Dr. Eric, to your room.

1:22:59.742 --> 1:23:03.179
He gives you an IV, a Z-Pak,
you get plenty of rest,

1:23:03.312 --> 1:23:05.481
you and your team
play the game,

1:23:06.815 --> 1:23:08.951
and you go number one
overall in April.

1:23:09.085 --> 1:23:10.486
All your dreams
come true.

1:23:10.619 --> 1:23:12.221
And...

1:23:12.355 --> 1:23:15.158
I will personally
make sure

1:23:15.291 --> 1:23:18.694
that the NCAA forms
an exploratory committee

1:23:18.827 --> 1:23:21.964
to fully monetize
amateur athletics.

1:23:22.098 --> 1:23:24.400
"Exploratory committee"?
Yeah, that's gonna
be a pass.

1:23:24.533 --> 1:23:27.536
[Katherine] No, wait.
You haven't heard
the cherry on top.

1:23:28.804 --> 1:23:30.973
Best part is,
you don't go to jail.

1:23:32.875 --> 1:23:35.211
[scoffs] For boycottin'
a football game?

1:23:35.344 --> 1:23:38.547
For the attempted murder
of K.C. Walton.

1:23:43.586 --> 1:23:44.953
[Emmett] Wow.

1:23:45.988 --> 1:23:47.890
Wow!

1:23:48.023 --> 1:23:51.460
For the last 48 hours,
you guys have been trying
to destroy this man!

1:23:51.594 --> 1:23:53.896
And what, you land
on outright assassination?

1:23:54.029 --> 1:23:57.233
For what, money?
K.C. Walton is blind
in one eye.

1:23:57.366 --> 1:23:59.402
He has a crack
in his skull,

1:23:59.535 --> 1:24:03.739
and he hasn't walked the same
ever since that fight
outside of the, uh,

1:24:03.872 --> 1:24:06.842
Gin Mill Bar and Grill.

1:24:08.877 --> 1:24:10.913
So I spoke to his mother,

1:24:11.046 --> 1:24:12.848
and she jumped at the idea
of being able to...
[whispers] It's bullshit.

1:24:12.981 --> 1:24:15.118
It's not bullshit!

1:24:15.251 --> 1:24:18.454
She jumped at the idea
of being able
to throw out that NDA

1:24:18.587 --> 1:24:21.357
and burn that 100K
that was used to buy them off

1:24:21.490 --> 1:24:23.926
if it meant that
she could find the guys

1:24:24.059 --> 1:24:26.929
who hurt her son
and get paid again.

1:24:27.062 --> 1:24:29.932
You don't know
what you're doing.
Hey. No.

1:24:31.200 --> 1:24:32.568
She ain't got nothin'.

1:24:32.701 --> 1:24:34.370
Let's get outta here.

1:24:36.339 --> 1:24:37.773
I got Reggie.

1:24:41.510 --> 1:24:43.179
Your half-brother.

1:24:48.184 --> 1:24:49.618
So you spoke to him?

1:24:51.187 --> 1:24:53.256
Haven't found him yet.

1:24:53.389 --> 1:24:56.859
When I do, I promise you,
I am going to piece together

1:24:56.992 --> 1:24:59.395
what exactly happened
that night.

1:24:59.528 --> 1:25:02.131
LeMarcus, wake up.

1:25:03.566 --> 1:25:06.369
How do you think
it is gonna look
when someone like Reggie,

1:25:06.502 --> 1:25:09.071
who has two felony
possession charges

1:25:09.205 --> 1:25:11.140
and assault and battery,
shows up

1:25:11.274 --> 1:25:13.342
in front of an all-white jury
in Missouri

1:25:13.476 --> 1:25:14.977
with
attempted-murder charges

1:25:15.110 --> 1:25:18.080
to a guy who is
permanently injured?

1:25:19.315 --> 1:25:21.317
One look at that jack,
and I'd be able to know

1:25:21.450 --> 1:25:23.352
that he was the one
that kicked K.C.'s ass.

1:25:24.287 --> 1:25:26.589
But guess what?
This is America.

1:25:26.722 --> 1:25:29.192
[whispers] Nobody cares
about your brother.

1:25:29.892 --> 1:25:30.959
Nobody.

1:25:32.728 --> 1:25:35.698
[normal voice] The only one
they were able to spot
that night in that melee

1:25:35.831 --> 1:25:39.702
was one LeMarcus James,
star quarterback.

1:25:39.835 --> 1:25:42.104
And so the state police
picked you up

1:25:42.238 --> 1:25:43.639
and hit you with charges,

1:25:43.772 --> 1:25:45.674
but some
deep-pocketed booster,

1:25:45.808 --> 1:25:47.910
who I think
I just fucking met,

1:25:48.043 --> 1:25:49.111
stepped in

1:25:49.245 --> 1:25:51.814
and paid off K.C.
and his family.

1:25:51.947 --> 1:25:53.949
Because that's what we do
in big football, right?

1:25:54.082 --> 1:25:56.585
You protect the phenom

1:25:56.719 --> 1:26:00.356
when he has a chance
of bringing home that
national title this year.

1:26:00.489 --> 1:26:02.358
Sound about right?

1:26:03.959 --> 1:26:07.796
I suggest you let
Dr. Eric patch you up tonight,

1:26:07.930 --> 1:26:11.467
and then we do
a joint press conference
in the morning.

1:26:11.600 --> 1:26:15.338
All the head honchos
up in the penthouse,

1:26:15.471 --> 1:26:17.139
heads bowed,

1:26:17.273 --> 1:26:19.808
agreeing that,
yes, there is a problem.

1:26:21.510 --> 1:26:23.178
And then you play.

1:26:23.312 --> 1:26:26.649
You win, and you get
to take that victory lap

1:26:26.782 --> 1:26:29.418
you have been
dreaming about since...

1:26:29.552 --> 1:26:31.854
since you stood
on the sidelines

1:26:31.987 --> 1:26:34.657
watching your big brother
in north Virginia.

1:26:36.191 --> 1:26:40.429
And then change does come
because of you, eventually.

1:26:40.563 --> 1:26:43.599
And that is something
you both can be proud of.

1:26:44.567 --> 1:26:47.236
I got a question.

1:26:47.370 --> 1:26:50.406
Are you completely
fucking heartless,
or just a little bit?

1:26:50.539 --> 1:26:53.041
Oh, my God.
[Emmett] How do you live
with yourself?

1:26:53.175 --> 1:26:56.979
Honestly, how do you live
with yourself?
[shouts] I am not heartless!

1:26:57.112 --> 1:26:58.981
You do not know me!

1:27:00.683 --> 1:27:03.486
You think I don't know
your struggle?

1:27:03.619 --> 1:27:07.290
You think I don't know
what you have come from?
That I haven't been there?

1:27:08.357 --> 1:27:10.058
You think I don't know
what it's like

1:27:10.192 --> 1:27:12.227
to be without heat
in your house?

1:27:12.361 --> 1:27:13.862
That I don't know
what it's like

1:27:13.996 --> 1:27:16.164
to not be able
to afford your jersey,

1:27:16.299 --> 1:27:17.800
and you are
avoiding your coach

1:27:17.933 --> 1:27:20.536
'cause you don't have
the $50 to pay for it?

1:27:22.237 --> 1:27:24.940
[voice breaking]
I ran track at Duke, okay?

1:27:26.375 --> 1:27:27.743
Full ride.

1:27:27.876 --> 1:27:29.812
No big medals, no big wins.

1:27:29.945 --> 1:27:33.282
But I took that money
because it was the only way
I was gonna run myself

1:27:33.416 --> 1:27:36.151
out of that
Red Hook project.

1:27:36.285 --> 1:27:38.887
[scoffs]
You think you know me.

1:27:40.255 --> 1:27:42.124
You don't know me.

1:27:42.257 --> 1:27:46.094
I had to fight and climb

1:27:46.228 --> 1:27:48.564
and crawl to be here

1:27:48.697 --> 1:27:50.699
because I did the work.

1:27:54.036 --> 1:27:59.074
The NCAA spends $3.6 billion

1:27:59.207 --> 1:28:02.778
on student-athlete
scholarships for kids like me,

1:28:02.911 --> 1:28:05.414
like you and like you,

1:28:06.782 --> 1:28:08.984
so that we can get a leg up.

1:28:09.117 --> 1:28:11.053
And what happens
to all of that

1:28:12.120 --> 1:28:14.122
when they start paying you?

1:28:14.256 --> 1:28:15.724
Hmm?

1:28:15.858 --> 1:28:20.095
What happens to volleyball
in Minnesota,

1:28:20.228 --> 1:28:22.130
to soccer in Idaho,

1:28:22.264 --> 1:28:24.433
to softball in South Carolina?

1:28:24.567 --> 1:28:26.935
What happens to
all of those other sports

1:28:27.069 --> 1:28:30.673
that are not men's football
and basketball?

1:28:32.675 --> 1:28:36.211
You out here fighting,
and you forgot
who you're fighting for.

1:28:38.781 --> 1:28:41.850
You know, but...
[clears throat, sighs]

1:28:42.951 --> 1:28:44.653
Hey, what do I know?

1:28:45.821 --> 1:28:47.289
I'm heartless.

1:29:00.736 --> 1:29:02.270
[door opens]

1:29:04.006 --> 1:29:05.474
[door closes]

1:29:09.111 --> 1:29:11.313
[crowd chattering]

1:29:24.627 --> 1:29:27.930
[on TV] Hi, everybody, and
good morning from the Big Easy.
I'm Steve Levy.

1:29:28.063 --> 1:29:29.698
We are some 12 hours away

1:29:29.832 --> 1:29:32.535
from tonight's Snickers
National Title game.

1:29:32.668 --> 1:29:34.703
Now, I'm being told
that a midnight deal

1:29:34.837 --> 1:29:37.372
may have been brokered
with LeMarcus James.

1:29:37.506 --> 1:29:40.275
Details still remain
a little bit sketchy,

1:29:40.409 --> 1:29:43.546
but there's
a news conference scheduled
for a couple hours from now.

1:29:43.679 --> 1:29:45.748
My sources tell me
that both teams

1:29:45.881 --> 1:29:47.382
could be
at full strength tonight,

1:29:47.516 --> 1:29:49.685
and that includes James.

1:29:49.818 --> 1:29:51.620
You know what else
that means?

1:29:51.754 --> 1:29:54.423
Strike up the band.
Fire up that old grill.

1:29:54.557 --> 1:29:56.992
We're gonna have some great
football action for you to--

1:29:57.125 --> 1:30:00.228
The 13-1 Cougars
against the undefeated Wolves,

1:30:00.362 --> 1:30:01.897
the two best players
in the country...

1:30:02.030 --> 1:30:04.600
Or will it?
Even with the rumors

1:30:04.733 --> 1:30:06.735
of a late-night deal
with LeMarcus James,

1:30:06.869 --> 1:30:10.205
many oddsmakers still doubt
he will actually play tonight.

1:30:10.338 --> 1:30:13.008
So the question is,
can James Lazor's Wolves

1:30:13.141 --> 1:30:15.010
win without
their star quarterback?

1:30:15.143 --> 1:30:16.612
I'm not so sure.

1:30:16.745 --> 1:30:20.348
Well, yeah.
He and LeMarcus
have the same mother.

1:30:20.483 --> 1:30:22.284
Yeah, they both grew up
in Virginia.

1:30:22.417 --> 1:30:25.454
Reggie,
he played JUCO football,

1:30:25.588 --> 1:30:27.289
but that fizzled out
after they cut him

1:30:27.422 --> 1:30:29.424
for having
too many concussions.

1:30:29.558 --> 1:30:31.426
I would start
with the state prisons.

1:30:31.560 --> 1:30:33.596
Even try
mental health facilities.

1:30:33.729 --> 1:30:35.831
We need to do
a social media backdoor too.

1:30:35.964 --> 1:30:37.766
I doubt that
he even has an account,

1:30:37.900 --> 1:30:40.135
but we have got to find him.
[knocking]

1:30:41.369 --> 1:30:43.138
He is our pressure point.

1:30:43.271 --> 1:30:45.608
Oh. Coach.

1:30:48.076 --> 1:30:49.645
I got your message.

1:30:53.649 --> 1:30:55.951
This thing
we're toying with,

1:30:57.620 --> 1:30:59.922
it's Pandora's box,
you know?

1:31:01.123 --> 1:31:02.290
I know.

1:31:02.424 --> 1:31:03.959
Nobody gets hurt.

1:31:05.193 --> 1:31:06.662
Nobody goes to jail.

1:31:06.795 --> 1:31:09.798
We just play this game.
That's what we all want.

1:31:17.773 --> 1:31:19.942
[coughing]

1:31:20.075 --> 1:31:22.110
[Emmett] Dear Lord,

1:31:22.244 --> 1:31:25.313
the trees are thick,
and we've yet to see a path
through the wilderness.

1:31:26.849 --> 1:31:28.617
Send us a light.

1:31:28.751 --> 1:31:30.953
Show us the way.
Amen.

1:31:31.086 --> 1:31:33.388
Amen. [coughing]

1:31:36.124 --> 1:31:39.327
I can't believe you've
been here this whole time
and didn't tell us.

1:31:39.461 --> 1:31:42.064
What? You thought I was
gonna miss the show?

1:31:42.197 --> 1:31:44.366
[LeMarcus chuckles quietly]

1:31:44.499 --> 1:31:45.901
I'm sorry.

1:31:46.034 --> 1:31:48.170
No, hey, you don't
owe me anything.

1:31:48.303 --> 1:31:50.673
You're the one, the two of you,
who had the guts and vision--

1:31:50.806 --> 1:31:53.008
I meant about her.

1:31:54.109 --> 1:31:56.178
Oh. [inhales sharply]

1:31:56.311 --> 1:31:57.780
Yeah. Her.

1:31:58.781 --> 1:31:59.982
Well...

1:32:00.115 --> 1:32:01.216
[inhales sharply]

1:32:01.349 --> 1:32:03.451
I made my own bed
on that one, so...

1:32:03.586 --> 1:32:05.888
"Thou shalt
not commit adultery"

1:32:06.021 --> 1:32:07.623
is the seventh Commandment.

1:32:10.959 --> 1:32:13.361
Thank you
for clarifying that, Emmett.

1:32:14.496 --> 1:32:16.164
You're welcome.

1:32:16.298 --> 1:32:19.301
[LeMarcus] Look, Elliott,
we can't thank you enough, man.

1:32:19.434 --> 1:32:22.137
Without you, we--
[sighs]

1:32:22.270 --> 1:32:24.673
we wouldn't have even had
a shot to pull this off.

1:32:26.508 --> 1:32:28.210
What's going on here?

1:32:29.745 --> 1:32:31.614
Are we about to hold hands

1:32:31.747 --> 1:32:33.849
and feel good
about your little protest?

1:32:33.982 --> 1:32:36.551
'Cause I thought you guys
were in it to win it.

1:32:36.685 --> 1:32:38.553
You know,
as if it were, say,

1:32:38.687 --> 1:32:41.123
the national title.

1:32:46.695 --> 1:32:50.232
Let me give you a little
something I stumbled across
from my travels.

1:32:51.934 --> 1:32:54.436
I believe that's your coach's.

1:32:55.604 --> 1:32:57.405
Wasn't even wrapped
in aluminum.

1:32:57.539 --> 1:32:59.875
Amateur move.

1:33:01.644 --> 1:33:04.446
Yeah, but what's
the point of this?
We can't unlock it.

1:33:05.848 --> 1:33:08.784
Do you need to?
You know what's on it.

1:33:10.252 --> 1:33:13.521
And you're a quarterback.
You know how to bluff
the other team.

1:33:19.327 --> 1:33:20.863
So you're saying
we keep going?

1:33:20.996 --> 1:33:22.464
[Elliott]
That's not my decision.

1:33:22.597 --> 1:33:24.967
It's not even
about which one is right.

1:33:26.869 --> 1:33:29.537
It's about, which one
are you gonna be able
to live with,

1:33:29.672 --> 1:33:31.740
no matter how it goes,

1:33:31.874 --> 1:33:34.009
how much you suffer
the consequences.

1:33:37.112 --> 1:33:40.783
I'm just letting you know
you still have some options.

1:33:40.916 --> 1:33:44.419
[coughing]
It's off to Rome for me,
comrades.

1:33:44.552 --> 1:33:47.455
Wait, you ain't staying
for the game?
Nah, opiate for the masses.

1:33:47.589 --> 1:33:50.192
It's, like,
too much winning
for my taste.

1:33:53.495 --> 1:33:55.330
I'm so proud
of you guys.

1:33:57.132 --> 1:33:58.801
You did this.

1:33:58.934 --> 1:34:01.169
You alone.
And it was...

1:34:03.571 --> 1:34:05.507
It was
fucking magnificent.

1:34:08.877 --> 1:34:10.645
Veni, vidi...

1:34:10.779 --> 1:34:12.147
Vici.
Vici.

1:34:12.280 --> 1:34:14.082
[door closes]
[coughing]

1:34:15.450 --> 1:34:16.685
[LeMarcus] Goddamn.

1:34:16.819 --> 1:34:18.120
Well...

1:34:19.755 --> 1:34:21.924
we're about due
for our surrender.

1:34:23.058 --> 1:34:24.793
What you thinkin'?

1:34:25.593 --> 1:34:27.162
I don't fucking know.

1:34:28.130 --> 1:34:29.631
My head is pounding.

1:34:29.765 --> 1:34:32.200
Where's that doc?

1:34:32.334 --> 1:34:35.203
Yeah, I'll go get him.
He said he'd wait
in the lobby.

1:34:36.538 --> 1:34:37.706
[coughing]

1:34:37.840 --> 1:34:39.474
Damn, you sick.

1:34:39.607 --> 1:34:42.677
See if I can get you
another IV.
I'll be back in ten.

1:34:47.382 --> 1:34:48.851
[door closes]

1:35:53.782 --> 1:35:57.285
[Mike] As soon as
he gets here, we'll have
the coach and him reunite,

1:35:57.419 --> 1:36:01.123
uh, pleasantries, and then
we'll get right to inviting
the media in.

1:36:01.256 --> 1:36:03.758
I'll give them a few minutes.
They'll go off to play.

1:36:03.892 --> 1:36:05.493
[knocking on door]

1:36:05.627 --> 1:36:06.962
Here we go.

1:36:09.531 --> 1:36:10.698
[Everly] Hey!

1:36:10.833 --> 1:36:13.268
LeMarcus has risen.
There he is.

1:36:13.401 --> 1:36:15.938
All right.
Great to see you.

1:36:16.071 --> 1:36:18.073
Can I get you something?
Some water? A Snickers?

1:36:18.206 --> 1:36:20.075
-[laughter]
-I'm good, thanks.

1:36:20.208 --> 1:36:22.644
[Mike] You were a little
under the weather,
but you're better now.

1:36:22.777 --> 1:36:24.412
Yeah.

1:36:24.546 --> 1:36:26.714
[Mike] That's good news.
[Wes] Not for us.

1:36:26.849 --> 1:36:28.150
[laughter]

1:36:28.283 --> 1:36:30.118
[Everly] True.

1:36:30.252 --> 1:36:32.220
[Mike] Um,
I just wanted to, uh,

1:36:32.354 --> 1:36:34.489
get us to have
a little face-to-face

1:36:34.622 --> 1:36:36.258
before we bring
the cameras in here.

1:36:36.391 --> 1:36:38.260
I was just telling
the coach here

1:36:38.393 --> 1:36:40.762
how impressed I was
with, uh, your conduct.

1:36:40.896 --> 1:36:42.130
Very honorable.

1:36:43.231 --> 1:36:44.599
[Coach Lazor] LeMarcus.

1:36:44.732 --> 1:36:46.501
The team is back.

1:36:47.569 --> 1:36:49.371
They heard
about this deal, and...

1:36:50.338 --> 1:36:51.874
everybody else
is playin' this.

1:36:52.007 --> 1:36:53.475
It's just you
and Emmett now.

1:36:53.608 --> 1:36:57.212
These gentlemen are
giving you a committee,

1:36:57.345 --> 1:37:00.315
and they are gonna address
all of your grievances.

1:37:01.616 --> 1:37:02.951
So,

1:37:03.818 --> 1:37:06.188
time to put on
those pads,

1:37:06.321 --> 1:37:08.123
join your brothers,
and do battle.

1:37:09.124 --> 1:37:10.692
Everybody's countin'
on you.

1:37:12.427 --> 1:37:14.362
I'm countin' on you.

1:37:17.799 --> 1:37:19.667
You know, I assure you,
LeMarcus,

1:37:19.801 --> 1:37:21.603
this isn't
a ceremonial committee.

1:37:21.736 --> 1:37:23.838
We're gonna dig down
into these issues

1:37:23.972 --> 1:37:26.875
and figure out
what's best for all of us.

1:37:29.744 --> 1:37:31.346
All right?

1:37:31.479 --> 1:37:33.548
Like the coach said,
we have a game to play.

1:37:33.681 --> 1:37:35.683
Let's get the cameras in...
I didn't say yes.

1:37:37.019 --> 1:37:38.720
[Everly]
What's that?

1:37:39.654 --> 1:37:40.989
I didn't say yes.

1:37:43.325 --> 1:37:45.160
[sighs]

1:37:47.662 --> 1:37:49.564
What would it take
in your mind

1:37:50.465 --> 1:37:52.400
to get to yes?

1:37:54.569 --> 1:37:56.704
Well, our demands
haven't changed.

1:38:01.243 --> 1:38:03.211
[chuckles]

1:38:32.207 --> 1:38:34.109
[Katherine] That's
the sealed case file

1:38:34.242 --> 1:38:36.544
from that fateful night
at the Gin Mill.

1:38:39.314 --> 1:38:43.085
The detectives investigated
for two weeks, and then...

1:38:43.218 --> 1:38:44.652
[sighs]

1:38:44.786 --> 1:38:49.257
...suddenly, K.C. Walton
decided to drop the charges.

1:38:55.597 --> 1:38:58.500
A lot of movin' pieces
in there, LeMarcus.

1:38:59.467 --> 1:39:01.303
This thing is a minefield.

1:39:03.105 --> 1:39:05.407
You find my brother yet?
[Katherine]
Getting close.

1:39:05.540 --> 1:39:09.644
I'd really love
to stop the search
and just have a beer,

1:39:10.778 --> 1:39:12.514
watch a football game.

1:39:16.118 --> 1:39:18.253
Well, why don't
we tell 'em, Coach?

1:39:19.587 --> 1:39:21.123
We're a wolf pack, right?

1:39:23.091 --> 1:39:24.993
We hunt together,
we starve alone.

1:39:25.127 --> 1:39:26.894
Ain't that the creed
you always preach?

1:39:27.029 --> 1:39:30.465
Why don't we tell everybody
how high up this really goes?

1:39:30.598 --> 1:39:32.500
Stop. Just stop.

1:39:32.634 --> 1:39:35.570
Look, you come out
of this now,

1:39:35.703 --> 1:39:37.939
you're not just
a Heisman Trophy winner,

1:39:38.073 --> 1:39:40.008
NFL first-rounder.

1:39:41.576 --> 1:39:44.812
You're an icon now.
You've already
accomplished that.

1:39:44.946 --> 1:39:47.949
You're the Curt Flood
of collegiate athletics.

1:39:49.117 --> 1:39:51.286
You're making
history here already.

1:39:51.419 --> 1:39:53.121
They're gonna write books
about you.

1:39:53.255 --> 1:39:55.557
Now, don't throw
everything away for-for

1:39:55.690 --> 1:39:58.193
whatever this
self-righteous bullshit is.

1:39:58.326 --> 1:39:59.961
Come on, man.
You've worked too hard.

1:40:00.095 --> 1:40:01.329
[grunts softly]

1:40:01.463 --> 1:40:03.798
We've worked too hard
for this.

1:40:04.832 --> 1:40:07.001
Let's just go
fuckin' win this thing.

1:40:08.670 --> 1:40:10.138
[scoffs]

1:40:10.272 --> 1:40:11.306
Win.

1:40:13.175 --> 1:40:15.410
That's all that
really matters, right?

1:40:17.145 --> 1:40:18.613
Just win.

1:40:20.182 --> 1:40:22.117
So that's what I did.

1:40:22.250 --> 1:40:24.519
I won every damn game I could.

1:40:25.953 --> 1:40:27.789
Conference championships,

1:40:27.922 --> 1:40:30.458
Heisman Trophy--
I won and I won and I won.

1:40:30.592 --> 1:40:35.029
Until you were so blind,
you didn't even see the game
I was really playin'.

1:40:35.163 --> 1:40:37.465
You see,
in order to slay Goliath,

1:40:37.599 --> 1:40:40.402
you gotta do it
on the biggest stage
with the brightest lights.

1:40:40.535 --> 1:40:42.970
Millions of people,
an entire system,

1:40:43.105 --> 1:40:45.907
so desperate
for one more win,

1:40:46.040 --> 1:40:47.675
they'd do anything,
give anything.

1:40:47.809 --> 1:40:50.512
No matter how many bodies
you gotta stand on top of.

1:40:51.646 --> 1:40:53.915
And then you got
your professor

1:40:54.048 --> 1:40:55.750
who's fuckin'
the coach's wife...

1:40:58.019 --> 1:40:59.754
to give you
everything you need.

1:41:01.856 --> 1:41:03.591
And you win.

1:41:03.725 --> 1:41:05.960
-You motherfucker!
-[excited chattering]

1:41:06.094 --> 1:41:08.730
You ungrateful bi...
Coach, don't do it.

1:41:08.863 --> 1:41:11.699
Goddamn you,
you fucking ungrateful...

1:41:12.900 --> 1:41:15.870
Jesus fucking Christ,
LeMarcus.

1:41:16.003 --> 1:41:18.940
My wife! My wife!

1:41:22.644 --> 1:41:24.412
[quietly]
Oh, my God.

1:41:29.817 --> 1:41:33.255
Jesus Christ, man.
Everything we've been
through together...

1:41:35.423 --> 1:41:37.559
everything
I've done for you...

1:41:40.228 --> 1:41:43.198
You were a pimply faced
little 16-year-old boy,

1:41:44.566 --> 1:41:46.601
scared to leave home.

1:41:48.770 --> 1:41:51.139
And I looked your mother
in the eyes,

1:41:51.273 --> 1:41:54.342
and I said,
"I will take care
of your boy."

1:41:54.476 --> 1:41:56.644
And that's
what I've done.

1:41:59.814 --> 1:42:01.616
Treated you like my own.

1:42:03.251 --> 1:42:05.086
Like my own son.

1:42:10.492 --> 1:42:12.126
How could you...

1:42:12.260 --> 1:42:13.761
[sighs]

1:42:13.895 --> 1:42:15.763
Goddamn, LeMarcus.

1:42:15.897 --> 1:42:17.932
[breathes shakily] Why?

1:42:22.637 --> 1:42:24.606
For all the ones
to come, Coach.

1:42:25.940 --> 1:42:27.842
The ones
who ain't as fortunate.

1:42:29.611 --> 1:42:31.679
Get this broken system
unbroken.

1:42:33.981 --> 1:42:35.917
So no more of us
get banged up

1:42:36.050 --> 1:42:38.186
and forced back
into poverty,

1:42:39.554 --> 1:42:41.589
just like what happened
to Reggie.

1:42:44.459 --> 1:42:48.129
You were the only one
who knew about that file.

1:42:48.263 --> 1:42:51.466
And you stoop even lower,
and you bring Reggie
into this?

1:42:53.000 --> 1:42:54.902
What, to you he's just...

1:42:55.036 --> 1:42:57.639
he's just some pawn
that you can use against me?

1:43:00.007 --> 1:43:01.643
He was my brother.

1:43:04.479 --> 1:43:06.180
He was a human being.

1:43:09.551 --> 1:43:12.920
Reggie died four months ago
in Tallahassee.

1:43:15.022 --> 1:43:16.324
He took his own life.

1:43:16.458 --> 1:43:19.261
[quietly] Oh, Jesus. Fuck.

1:43:19.394 --> 1:43:22.230
Y'all didn't know.
And what's worse,
y'all don't even care.

1:43:24.332 --> 1:43:26.167
There's always
some new batch of kids

1:43:26.301 --> 1:43:29.036
that get you more wins
and get you more money.

1:43:33.007 --> 1:43:34.342
I am not your son.

1:43:35.810 --> 1:43:37.144
I'm a man.

1:43:39.547 --> 1:43:41.048
[sniffles]

1:43:42.984 --> 1:43:44.419
Yeah, you are.

1:43:49.524 --> 1:43:51.158
And I love you.

1:43:56.097 --> 1:43:58.132
But I got
a football game to win.

1:44:02.437 --> 1:44:04.071
[door opens]

1:44:05.440 --> 1:44:06.874
[door closes]

1:44:12.380 --> 1:44:14.416
[Mike clears throat]
Gentlemen, um,

1:44:14.549 --> 1:44:16.250
would you step out
for a minute?

1:44:17.385 --> 1:44:18.886
Give us some time?

1:44:20.254 --> 1:44:21.589
[sniffles]

1:44:39.374 --> 1:44:42.910
You open up that minefield,
it's gonna be more
than just me and Reggie.

1:44:44.178 --> 1:44:45.780
On Coach's phone,
we got emails

1:44:45.913 --> 1:44:48.049
from prosecutors,
law enforcement.

1:44:48.182 --> 1:44:50.718
All of 'em were involved
in the cover-up.

1:44:50.852 --> 1:44:53.087
Shoot, even the governor

1:44:53.220 --> 1:44:55.623
chest bumps
in the locker room
on game day.

1:44:57.392 --> 1:45:00.862
Coach's phone,
you'll find a text where
he promises to take care of it.

1:45:05.633 --> 1:45:07.001
The martyr.

1:45:08.336 --> 1:45:10.838
Willing to die
for the cause.

1:45:10.972 --> 1:45:13.675
I find that courageous.
Admirable.

1:45:15.076 --> 1:45:17.679
But what about Emmett Sunday?

1:45:18.813 --> 1:45:21.015
You said you were
doing this for him.

1:45:22.750 --> 1:45:24.151
Miss Poe?

1:45:36.163 --> 1:45:37.532
[Katherine clears throat]

1:45:37.665 --> 1:45:40.935
"It was chaos.
People everywhere.

1:45:41.068 --> 1:45:44.005
Then all of a sudden,
LeMarcus James,
the quarterback,

1:45:44.138 --> 1:45:46.974
showed up
with someone else.

1:45:48.510 --> 1:45:52.146
[clears throat] A big guy.
It was really dangerous.

1:45:52.279 --> 1:45:54.181
Then the big white guy

1:45:55.583 --> 1:45:58.052
flew through the crowd
and hit one guy

1:45:58.185 --> 1:46:01.355
who dropped like he was dead
and threw another guy
into a wall.

1:46:01.489 --> 1:46:04.659
LeMarcus grabbed the man
the crew were beating on,

1:46:04.792 --> 1:46:06.428
and everyone ran.

1:46:07.629 --> 1:46:10.231
Like I said,
it was chaos."
That was self-defense.

1:46:11.332 --> 1:46:13.401
[Mike]
Maybe so. Maybe so.

1:46:14.402 --> 1:46:15.703
But does it matter?

1:46:17.238 --> 1:46:19.707
We go down this road,

1:46:19.841 --> 1:46:21.909
they won't be putting you
on trial,

1:46:22.043 --> 1:46:24.712
they'll be putting
your best friend, Emmett.

1:46:25.847 --> 1:46:29.216
Now, do you have the stomach
to watch the sharks

1:46:29.350 --> 1:46:31.486
rip him apart limb by limb

1:46:31.619 --> 1:46:35.022
in front of the whole world
and leave him destroyed,

1:46:35.156 --> 1:46:36.323
canceled?

1:46:38.392 --> 1:46:40.428
LeMarcus,
you're standing toe-to-toe
with the behemoth,

1:46:40.562 --> 1:46:42.564
and we haven't even
begun to fight.

1:46:44.532 --> 1:46:46.768
College football is more
important than you,

1:46:46.901 --> 1:46:48.870
me, Emmett,

1:46:49.003 --> 1:46:51.038
or whatever really is
on that phone.

1:46:52.674 --> 1:46:54.676
The American people

1:46:54.809 --> 1:46:57.111
will let the state
of Missouri
fall under the sea

1:46:57.244 --> 1:46:58.846
rather than give up
Saturday afternoon,

1:46:58.980 --> 1:47:00.682
drunk and roaring
for their alma mater.

1:47:02.950 --> 1:47:04.952
We're inevitable
as the rain.

1:47:12.426 --> 1:47:14.662
Now, you gonna put
on that helmet or not?

1:47:23.270 --> 1:47:25.840
[crowd cheering]

1:47:29.276 --> 1:47:32.547
[sportscaster on TV] ...gearing
up for the college football
national title game.

1:47:32.680 --> 1:47:34.381
The fans are buzzing
with excitement...

1:47:34.516 --> 1:47:37.151
[Emmett] "Inevitable"?
Like what?

1:47:38.553 --> 1:47:39.887
The rain.

1:47:41.723 --> 1:47:44.091
"I'm inevitable
as the rain."

1:47:46.360 --> 1:47:48.630
Feels powerful.
Mm-hmm.

1:47:48.763 --> 1:47:50.397
It was.

1:47:54.802 --> 1:47:56.170
[bones popping]

1:47:56.303 --> 1:47:58.072
[sighs]

1:47:58.205 --> 1:48:01.142
Gonna have to drain
the fluid out of this
damn thing again.

1:48:04.912 --> 1:48:07.381
You look better. Lighter.

1:48:07.515 --> 1:48:09.450
Finally breathe
through my nose.

1:48:10.618 --> 1:48:13.821
By the way,
that Doc Holliday head fake,

1:48:13.955 --> 1:48:16.658
you playing like you were
on your deathbed,
was sure good.

1:48:17.592 --> 1:48:19.460
[scoffs]

1:48:19.594 --> 1:48:23.064
Lacked the nuance of Kilmer,
but, uh, I bought it.

1:48:24.031 --> 1:48:25.667
I'll be your Huckleberry.

1:48:25.800 --> 1:48:28.235
[both chuckle]

1:48:34.609 --> 1:48:36.844
You sure they didn't try
to use me against you?

1:48:36.978 --> 1:48:38.179
Nah.

1:48:39.614 --> 1:48:41.282
I swear.

1:48:41.415 --> 1:48:43.517
'Cause if I find out
that you were...

1:48:43.651 --> 1:48:45.219
Trust me.

1:48:45.352 --> 1:48:48.155
They know this fight hurts them
way more than it hurts us.

1:48:48.289 --> 1:48:52.026
All those people involved
in the cover-up,
they ain't doin' shit.

1:48:52.159 --> 1:48:55.362
[Levy] The Superdome
in New Orleans is ready
to explode with excitement.

1:48:55.496 --> 1:48:58.299
Tonight, it's the Snickers
National Title game.

1:48:58.432 --> 1:49:00.167
Hi, everybody,
and good evening.

1:49:00.301 --> 1:49:02.236
I'm Steve Levy,
along with Malcolm Jenkins,

1:49:02.369 --> 1:49:03.838
and this one has
all the makings.

1:49:03.971 --> 1:49:05.539
This could be a classic.
No.

1:49:05.673 --> 1:49:07.074
[Levy] We're talking about
for years to come...

1:49:07.208 --> 1:49:09.443
Leave it.
...for a variety
of reasons.

1:49:09.577 --> 1:49:11.378
A lot of the controversy
still looms

1:49:11.512 --> 1:49:13.581
with LeMarcus James bein'
missin' from the action,

1:49:13.715 --> 1:49:16.350
as he continues his fight
against the NCAA practices,

1:49:16.483 --> 1:49:18.753
a stance that has gone
crazy on social media...
Whoo. Yes, sir.

1:49:18.886 --> 1:49:20.622
...with the viral hashtag,
"Fix the System."

1:49:20.755 --> 1:49:22.790
[Levy] How about
one million tweets

1:49:22.924 --> 1:49:24.959
the last 12 hours alone?

1:49:25.092 --> 1:49:27.428
My sense is,
this is only the beginning.

1:49:27.561 --> 1:49:31.132
How do you think that translates
onto the field the next
60 minutes we'll see tonight?

1:49:31.265 --> 1:49:33.467
[Jenkins] I think
you'll see these coaches
have these teams prepared.

1:49:33.601 --> 1:49:35.402
These players have worked
so hard to get to this moment,

1:49:35.536 --> 1:49:37.071
that I think
they'll be focused...

1:49:37.204 --> 1:49:38.773
At least we made
some noise, right?

1:49:38.906 --> 1:49:40.775
...knowing that
this is everything...

1:49:40.908 --> 1:49:42.744
Oh, that wasn't just noise.

1:49:44.145 --> 1:49:46.247
The truth is out now
because of us.

1:49:47.414 --> 1:49:48.950
And they can't hide it.

1:49:50.317 --> 1:49:52.920
Now more people are gonna
stand up, a lot more.

1:49:54.021 --> 1:49:56.523
And they'll know
right where to hit 'em.

1:49:57.591 --> 1:49:58.760
Yeah.

1:50:00.662 --> 1:50:01.763
Yeah.

1:50:02.596 --> 1:50:03.931
Hell, yeah.

1:50:04.065 --> 1:50:06.734
Man, we're like the Rebels
in Rogue One.

1:50:09.370 --> 1:50:11.906
We die on the beach,

1:50:12.039 --> 1:50:15.142
but the plans
for the Death Star
make it off the island.

1:50:23.217 --> 1:50:25.486
Nothing is inevitable
except the truth.
